Lee Vining first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Lee Vining had a population of 217. The population density was {{convert|41.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Lee Vining was 104 (47.9%) [[White Americans|White]], 3 (1.4%) [[African Americans|African American]], 22 (10.1%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 35 (16.1%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 53 (24.4%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 109 persons (50.2%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Lee Vining CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0640998 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 24, 2025}}</ref>

The census reported that 203 people (93.5% of the population) lived in households, 14 (6.5%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and no one was institutionalized.<ref name=DP1/>

[[File:Old Church In Lee Vining - panoramio.jpg|thumb|Old Church In Lee Vining, 2015]]
There were 88 households, out of which 30 (34.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 43 (48.9%) were married-couple households, 8 (9.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 20 (22.7%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 17 (19.3%) had a male householder with no partner present. 33 households (37.5%) were one person, and 15 (17.0%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.31.<ref name=DP1/> There were 50 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (56.8% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Lee Vining CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0640998 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 24, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 46 people (21.2%) under the age of 18, 17 people (7.8%) aged 18 to 24, 52 people (24.0%) aged 25 to 44, 64 people (29.5%) aged 45 to 64, and 38 people (17.5%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 42.5{{nbsp}}years.    For every 100 females, there were 88.7 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 114 housing units at an average density of {{convert|21.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 88 (77.2%) were occupied. Of these, 37 (42.0%) were owner-occupied, and 51 (58.0%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

